<subSubSection id="4C36664C9F57B3DFF253DC3C101F4D5C" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="D3F7F19E087E43CDB2E69F590AC85976" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="718511F955B45CA0B0BCA21FDCFD2D0B" authority="Scopoli" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthrax" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anthrax Scopoli</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9B585AD1CBF98C88BB34FC94795EC859" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="232F943A4FAFC427B109AC141A59AFFA" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13056A5DE42475D6455C7C4857F92178" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
This is a diverse genus with 248 species worldwide. Two old but complete revisions of the genus, including distribution maps and keys, were made by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76140B3B1999AB55FA363D700275F83" author="Marston, N" journalOrPublisher="Technical Bulletin of the Kansas State University Agricultural Experiment Station" pageId="30" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 79" title="A revision of the Nearctic species of the albofasciatus group of the genus Anthrax Scopoli (Diptera: Bombyliidae)." volume="127" year="1963">Marston (1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="25912E980FB8CFE10E6AC5400A4CEB12" author="Marston, N" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C." pageId="30" pageNumber="79" title="Revision of New World species of Anthrax (Diptera: Bombyliidae), other than the Anthrax albofasciatus group." url="10.5479/si.00810282.43" year="1970">1970</bibRefCitation>
). Thanks to these 
<taxonomicName id="6A8B72CBC3E112F19760E720B07E874A" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthrax" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anthrax</taxonomicName>
species can be easily identified. Some 
<taxonomicName id="A97BFFBDB671D080F9A94BCF6A1B3DF1" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthrax" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anthrax</taxonomicName>
species are widely distributed occupying two biogeographic regions. From the seven 
<taxonomicName id="4F06FDB4C3FBF1D1D75965500CE2B17F" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthrax" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anthrax</taxonomicName>
species collected in this study in Coahuila, just 
<taxonomicName id="3E485FCA8F75D684FB27628F997449BC" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthrax cybele" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cybele">Anthrax cybele</taxonomicName>
(Coquillett, 1894) has a restricted distribution. The other six species are widespread across the Nearctic region. Two species of 
<taxonomicName id="5C77E8B17A596761EF5012FB785507F2" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthrax" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anthrax</taxonomicName>
are reported for the first time for Mexico.
</paragraph>
